e\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9999999999126885, \"rank\": 8.713630089772526e-11, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Boxing presents itself as an alternative to the troubled and controversial IBA, and hopes to organise Olympic boxing events in the future.\", \"from\": 7013, \"to\": 7157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7094, \"end\": 7097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.95448574307401, \"rank\": 0.04768458539736475, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IOC rules on gender eligibility  The advice published by the IOC in 2021 to help give governing bodies support in determining rules around gender eligibility stated that no athlete should be excluded from competing based on an \\\"unverified, alleged or perceived unfair competitive advantage due to their sex variations, physical appearance and/or transgender status.\\\"\", \"from\": 7159, \"to\": 7525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7220, \"end\": 7223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.83653093311564e-46, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC document is not legally binding, but it clearly states what it expects from governing bodies responsible for regulating their own sports.\", \"from\": 7527, \"to\": 7672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7531, \"end\": 7534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.83653093311564e-46, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Athletes should be allowed to compete but unfair advantage needs to be regulated,\\\" the IOC document says.\", \"from\": 7674, \"to\": 7780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7762, \"end\": 7765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.83653093311564e-46, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Time  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 7782, \"to\": 7805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 7806, \"to\": 7896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7831, \"end\": 7854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 7856, \"end\": 7863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999989599928, \"rank\": 5.61840253356469e-10, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.\", \"from\": 